V2 System Architecture Expansion
1. Trait Intensity

Each Trait can have an intensity value (e.g., 1-10 scale or percentage)
Intensity affects the strength or expression of associated Qualities
Intensity can vary when the same Trait comes from different Archetypes
Control flow:

During Persona creation, calculate final Trait intensity (especially for Traits from multiple Archetypes)
Apply intensity modifiers to Quality effects
Allow for intensity changes over time through events or experiences



2. Quality Interactions

Define interaction types between Qualities (enhancement, suppression, transformation, etc.)
Create an interaction matrix or rule set for Quality pairs/groups
Control flow:

When a Quality state changes (enabled/disabled), check for interactions with other active Qualities
Apply interaction effects (modify Quality strength, disable conflicting Qualities, enable synergistic Qualities)
Recalculate Quality effects when their interaction dependencies change



3. Situational Archetypes

Define Situational Archetypes that represent context-dependent templates
Situational Archetypes have their own Traits but are only activated in specific contexts
Control flow:

Define conditions for Situational Archetype activation
When conditions are met, temporarily apply Situational Archetype Traits to Persona
Calculate resulting Quality changes based on temporary Traits
Remove Situational effects when conditions no longer apply



4. Derived Situations

Create a system for dynamic situation generation based on combinations of:

Environmental factors
Persona state (active Qualities and Traits)
Presence of other Personas


Control flow:

Regularly evaluate context to identify potential Situations
When Situation conditions are met, apply associated effects to relevant Personas
Track active Situations and their effects
Manage transitions between Situations, including gradual changes



5. Integration Layer

Create a system to manage interactions between these new components
Handle priority and precedence (e.g., which effects take precedence when conflicts arise)
Maintain state consistency when multiple systems are affecting Traits and Qualities
Control flow:

Define evaluation order for the different systems
Implement conflict resolution for contradictory effects
Create hooks for future V2 expansions
